node.text:
A spectacular Mammatus clouds formation in a sunset sky over New Mexico 😍

These distinct bulges or pouches are formed by cold air sinking down to form the pockets contrary to the puffs of clouds rising through the convection of warm air. Mammatus clouds often form in association with Cumulonimbus clouds, which usually indicate severe thunderstorms due to their huge mass of unstable air. This could also mean that there is a chance of hail, heavy rain and lightning in the vicinity.

Capture date: May 2012

📷 Brad Hannon - Photography @bradhannon

📍Located at 2546m above sea level, Kapuche Glacier lake is the lowest altitude glacier lake in Nepal.

Video speed x 2.5 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

The collision of two galaxies! This beautiful yet violent phenomenon is bigger than humanity's scale and can take up to millions and even billions of years🌌🌌

Did you know?
Our galaxy, The Milky Way, and Andromeda, the nearest galaxy, are getting closer to each other and will collide in around 4.5 billion years🤯😱

The maximum number of photographs captured on Solar Eclipse by an individual is 500 and this record was set by Sham Shankar Bhat S N (born on July 29, 1999) of Shimoga, Karnataka, India. He captured the different phases of the sun and the moon and also made a collage of all the photographs on December 26, 2019.
